      <h1>Ownership</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        How the legal estate is owned and the disclosure that owning it
        entails. The shape of the disclosure depends on the tenure: a
        freehold owner answers a short set of questions, a leaseholder a
        much longer one, and a managed (share-of-freehold / commonhold)
        owner a third. Each branch below scopes its own cluster.
      </p>
      <h2 id="subpages">Pages in this cluster</h2>
      <ul class="cluster-index">
        <li><a href="/schema/legal-estate/ownership/freehold"><strong>Freehold</strong></a> — freehold-specific ownership disclosure.</li>
        <li><a href="/schema/legal-estate/ownership/leasehold"><strong>Leasehold</strong></a> — lease term, contacts, management, ground rent, service charge, consents and assorted leasehold legal artefacts.</li>
        <li><a href="/schema/legal-estate/ownership/managed"><strong>Managed</strong></a> — share-of-freehold / commonhold ownership: contacts, transfer, service charge, insurance, disputes and documents.</li>
      </ul>
